<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="210" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 <gloss target="#t_PAA1">PAA</gloss>/7–1747: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-17T19:00:00-03:00">July 17,
                                    1947—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>880. Ferreira interviewed today re route patterns of bilateral
                            stated:</p>
                        <p>During his absences Diaz Bialet’s uncontrolled activities increased
                                <gloss target="#t_FAMA1">FAMA</gloss> disorganization. New board
                            will be elected August 18, route patterns will be ready then. Delay due
                            entirely <gloss target="#t_FAMA1">FAMA</gloss> disorganization.
                            Considers it advisable and hopes we not press decision till August <pb facs="0264" n="248" xml:id="pg_248"/> 18. Alternative is govt to
                            govt negotiation since basis Argentine reply not ready immediate result
                            unlikely. Agreed meantime problems will be solved in “spirit of
                            agreement signed by both countries”.</p>
                        <p>Embassy believes necessary await August 18 for route decision and in view
                            “spirit of agreement” statement agrees procedure suggested <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 650, July 14<note n="55" xml:id="d210fn1">Not printed.</note> when <gloss target="#t_Panagra1">Panagra</gloss> plans approved by board.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ray</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>